news.title: Property sales in Indore may touch record high this fiscal
news.para: In January, over 12,000 properties were registered in Indore district that generated revenue of Rs 153 crore, according to the official data.

news.title: Satellite towns proposed to reduce urbanisation load on Shimla
news.para: In the transit oriented development proposal of bypass road and its integration with existing and new development — counter magnet town and satellite towns — are also on the cards.

news.title: Pune: Land developer booked after NRI's complaint
news.para: Police said the NRI stated in his complaint that he had invested money in the Boat Club Road township project in 2015. The land developer and his partner, however, sold the scheme and his share to another builder, keeping him in the dark about the step, the complaint stated.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's standing panel rejects proposal to hike property tax
news.para: Bhoyar also said the NMC will waive property tax of citizens having 500 sq ft properties only if the state government provides additional funds.

news.title: East Delhi civic body scraps proposal to impose new taxes
news.para: Earlier, the standing committee of the BJP-led East Delhi Municipal Corporation (EDMC) on December 29 last had rejected the proposal in the budget to increase property tax levied on residential and commercial properties.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Property tax relief for newly merged areas
news.para: Most of the residents of these newly merged areas were slapped with property tax bills that were 2.5 times their usual bills when they lived under nagarpalika or gram panchayat jurisdiction.

news.title: Lucknow development body to annul allotment of absentees
news.para: However, most of them are not either taking the calls or showing interest in taking the allotment letter, hence LDA is now planning to cancel allotment of these people and give them to those in the waiting list.

news.title: Awfis leases 85,000 sq ft space in Noida
news.para: Currently Awfis has 11 coworking centres in the Delhi-NCR region and the company plans to open 10-15 more centres in the market the by end of 2022.

news.title: Cement prices likely to stay firm in Q4 after staying buoyant in January
news.para: In the recent past, cement prices did not see any major increase as companies were unable to peg the demand trend. However, this is likely to change given a sustained push to demand. In January, companies increased prices by 2-5% compared with the previous month.

news.title: Prestige Group set to buy TVS' Anna Salai property for Rs 600 crore
news.para: A mix of retail and commercial Grade A office space is likely to come up on the 89-ground plot that is on the road that connects Anna Salai to White’s Road, according to sources close to the development.

news.title: Noida authority's CEO to meet all stakeholders for roadmap to raze Supertech twin towers
news.para: The meeting will be attended by officials from the district administration, police, discom PVVNL, Gas Authority of India Ltd (GAIL), the state pollution control board, the controller of explosives, Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) and the RWAs of both Emerald Court and ATS Greens Village, which is the immediate neighbour of the twin towers.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC asked for refund plan for Green View homebuyers
news.para: Gurgaon’s outgoing deputy commissioner Yash Garg directed NBCC to come back with a concrete proposal regarding repairs or refund of money to the homebuyers before initiating any action for eviction.

news.title: SC asks AG to submit guidelines to regulate land allotment to housing societies
news.para: A bench comprising Chief Justice N V Ramana and Justices A S Bopanna and Hima Kohli said that now the scope of the petition has been expanded, the plea may be listed after the AG submits guidelines, proposed by him, to govern the allotment of land to housing societies nationwide.

news.title: Sebi to auction seven properties of Saradha Realty on February 22
news.para: Inviting bids for sale of properties in the recovery proceedings against Saradha Realty and its promoters/ directors, Sebi said the e-auction will take place on February 22, 2022.

news.title: UK housing boom starts to fade as cost-of-living squeeze tightens: Halifax
news.para: Russell Galley, managing director at Halifax, said "it remains likely that the rate of house price growth will slow considerably over the next year" even as the limited supply of houses for sale will provide some support to prices.
